Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.50,0:00:03.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Don't come!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.50,0:00:08.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.67,0:00:10.30,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Why is that dog glowing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.46,0:00:11.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's a demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.67,0:00:13.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Demon dogs really do exist!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.93,0:00:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's phosphorus.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.76,0:00:21.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phosphorus has the property to emit a bluish\Nwhite glow upon exposure to oxygen; you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.56,0:00:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They just painted the dog with it to\Nmake it glow and frighten people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.36,0:00:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez don't just spoil the ending like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.94,0:00:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Holmes' The Hound of the Baskervilles is really popular...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.99,0:00:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I thought you already knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.70,0:00:36.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now look here...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.91,0:00:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Shinichi, we aren't Holmes geeks!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.91,0:00:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that we know the demon dog's\Na fake, there's no point in watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.75,0:00:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll watch another channel!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.04,0:00:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, how about joinin' us on a real demon dog hunt?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.88,0:00:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Kazuha chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.23,0:02:57.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,THE VICTIM IS KUDOU SHINICHI
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.46,0:03:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We did ring the bell, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.63,0:03:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't answer, and we heard screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.76,0:03:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since your front door is unlocked...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.47,0:03:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even so, there's no reason for you to just barge in!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.06,0:03:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.52,0:03:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by "demon dog"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:16.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just some random made-up story.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.94,0:03:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't know that just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.94,0:03:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.24,0:03:25.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About five years ago, an extremely rich\Nelder named Inubushi Tsunechika died.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.53,0:03:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.95,0:03:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, he was the president of the Inubushi Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.66,0:03:33.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be the president was killed by the demon dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.08,0:03:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.21,0:03:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just died of an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.71,0:03:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He apparently had terminal cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.25,0:03:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, about that president...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.38,0:03:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that he had lots of energy and\Nwas a womanizer when he was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.59,0:03:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little while after he died, a lot of people visited his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.27,0:03:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were all saying, "l'm a child\Nconnected to the president by blood!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.39,0:03:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Illegitimate children?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.52,0:03:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.48,0:03:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each one of them had a picture of their mother with the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.36,0:04:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't something like that just be\Na lie in order to get the inheritance?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.03,0:04:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.66,0:04:09.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if they wanted to confirm it, the\Nold man himself is already gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.24,0:04:12.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since they each said their own mother died as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.83,0:04:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They couldn't learn about the romance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally they'd be turned away at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.79,0:04:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the president's wife by the name of Satomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.88,0:04:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She accepted them all as her adopted children.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.30,0:04:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All eight of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.89,0:04:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eight of them!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.47,0:04:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now that the wife has been struck with illness, the case begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.19,0:04:36.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A case of inheritance...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.77,0:04:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.73,0:04:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The huge inheritance the wife received from the president...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.15,0:04:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to be divided among the eight\Nadopted children upon her death.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.07,0:04:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But two of the children have died in bizarre ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.66,0:04:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them fell from a cliff, and said this just before dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.04,0:04:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That what pushed him off was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:05:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something akin to a monster with a body engulfed\Nin crimson flames that grew bigger as it attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.88,0:05:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An apparition that strongly resembled a dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.26,0:05:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was prob√¢bly someone who set a\Nplastic doll on fire and chased after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.35,0:05:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.69,0:05:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy fled from the dog by bike for as far as one kilometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.65,0:05:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would've noticed, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.44,0:05:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, was Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} contacted by that Inubushi family?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, one of the adopted children is an\Nacquaintance of Kazuha's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.20,0:05:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\ I heard they were elementary schoolmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.71,0:05:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he used to live in Kansai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.42,0:05:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he's saying that the two people who died were killed by a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.30,0:05:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A curse?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.88,0:05:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to him, one of the eight children is an imposter\Nwho holds a grudge against the Inubushi family...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And plans to use a cursed demon dog to\Nroot out all those with Inubushi blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.77,0:05:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Root out!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.90,0:06:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, it was my dad, the chief detective with the\NOsaka Police, who he really wanted to consult with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.24,0:06:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no way my dad can leave Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.45,0:06:12.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having no choice, he asked if someone\Ncould at least come and listen to his story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.12,0:06:13.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's where I step in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.58,0:06:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But all in all, you still need to go to that Inubushi house, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.21,0:06:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he gave up all claim to the\Ninheritance and left the Inubushi family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.09,0:06:28.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has since changed his name back to his\Nmother's maiden name and lives here in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.01,0:06:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go listen to his story tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.72,0:06:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.30,0:06:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys wanna come?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.81,0:06:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, that guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.43,0:06:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has a reall hilarious name!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.23,0:06:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou Shinichi"!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.48,0:06:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.75,0:06:47.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, isn't it hilarious?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.15,0:06:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.28,0:06:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this may I ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.12,0:06:55.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A detective who was summoned by Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.99,0:06:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a woman's voice just now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.33,0:07:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't that person live alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.08,0:07:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has a bad back, so he has a lady come to\Nlook after him two to three times a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.92,0:07:10.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he can't even go to work at his company now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.74,0:07:16.47,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Abukawa Funae (39)\NHome Helper
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:14.22,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:16.47,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is sleeping right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.39,0:07:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.81,0:07:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.44,0:07:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sound alseep, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.61,0:07:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't this room a bit too warm?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.86,0:07:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.87,0:07:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seems to have a slight cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.58,0:07:41.33,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kudou Shinichi (43)\NAdopted Son of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.70,0:07:41.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Also, he said he didn't sleep much at all last night\Nbecause he stayed up doing a lot of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.50,0:07:44.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But I think he should wake up soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.54,0:07:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, allow us to stay here until he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.17,0:07:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please listen to what he has to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.80,0:07:55.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think I can handle it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.68,0:08:00.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd rather die now and be at peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.43,0:08:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he really say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.02,0:08:03.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.52,0:08:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying that if he were going to be eaten by a cursed demon dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.02,0:08:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man may have seen it as well, I mean the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.57,0:08:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.53,0:08:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, I'm going to go buy groceries for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.95,0:08:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you two watch the-house for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.08,0:08:26.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cursed demon dog, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.33,0:08:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, did you hear anything else about the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.88,0:08:34.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I heard about the names of those eight adopted children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:37.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the pronounciations are...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.72,0:08:42.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, Takako, Saki, Tomoaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.77,0:08:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miwako, Yoshiya, Keiji, and Miyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.98,0:08:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they were all named by...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.69,0:08:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,President Inubushi Tsunechika who died five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.07,0:08:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, who were the-two people that died?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.74,0:08:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if I recall...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.70,0:09:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.71,0:09:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he may have set a timer to play\Nmusic instead of an alarm clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.67,0:09:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This door...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.38,0:09:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been sealed with duct tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.15,0:09:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suicide by charcoal?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.02,0:09:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.15,0:09:32.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of the taped window.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.73,0:09:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'll get the grill out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.70,0:09:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, this is stuck on really tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't he have back problems!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.91,0:09:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even made a footstool out of books...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.42,0:09:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This charcoal grill...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.17,0:09:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.84,0:09:59.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's carbon monoxide poisoning!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.64,0:10:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move from there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.01,0:10:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't come inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.44,0:10:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We first came to this room about thirty minutes ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.03,0:10:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His jaw has started to stiffen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.24,0:10:23.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His back is showing slight livor mortis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.99,0:10:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, this charcoal...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.50,0:10:30.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that footstool made from stacked books.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.08,0:10:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.46,0:10:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.55,0:10:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway I should...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.09,0:10:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.76,0:10:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before you do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:43.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have just one question for you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.47,0:10:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you kill that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.31,0:10:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's our line.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.73,0:10:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're telling us it was the demon dog's curse...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.19,0:10:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You won't fool us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.95,0:11:06.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait just a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.45,0:11:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would I be the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.96,0:11:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just an ordinary caretaker...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.04,0:11:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I only returned from shopping just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.46,0:11:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, it looks as if this door was sealed with duct tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.97,0:11:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when I got here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.59,0:11:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were tearing the seals off of the window, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.85,0:11:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was stuck on there real good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.68,0:11:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention the fact that a charcoal grill was next to the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.06,0:11:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, no matter how you look at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.98,0:11:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a charcoal-burning suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.36,0:11:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That may be so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.65,0:11:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both the entry door and the window were sealed from the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.08,0:11:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making it a perfectly sealed-room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.87,0:11:52.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the interior of the room were filled with carbon monoxide...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.67,0:11:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be impossible for anyone else to be in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.46,0:11:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.96,0:11:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, it is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.17,0:12:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s having a bad back...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:06.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a footstool made from books in the lower part of the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.51,0:12:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think some with a bad back\Nwould've deliberately bent over...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.06,0:12:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And taken books from such a low shelf?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:21.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if the books on the shelves he could easily\Nreach were the ones he didn't want to step on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.03,0:12:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he forced himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.57,0:12:24.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention this charcoal...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.03,0:12:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't hot even if I hold it in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.20,0:12:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You may not know this, little boy, but the charcoal...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.04,0:12:32.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you burn charcoal in an airtight room...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.29,0:12:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The oxygen in the air will be exhausted, causing incomplete\Ncombustion and carbon monoxide is generated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.13,0:12:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If inhaled, carbon monoxide will\Nintroduce itself to the bloodstream...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.09,0:12:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Combine with the hemoglobin and lead\Nto asphyxiation followed by death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.30,0:12:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.64,0:12:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want to say that when the oxygen was finally\Nused up, the flame on the charcoal went out?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.81,0:12:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.48,0:13:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it would've been extremely painful if\Nfailed, followed by serious after-effects...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.86,0:13:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I don't know what charcoal suiciders might be thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.36,0:13:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was about thirty minutes ago that we\Nlast saw this man sleeping in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.12,0:13:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he then sealed the door and window,\Nwouldn't it take more than ten minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.50,0:13:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would take even longer if he took it slow with his bad back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.50,0:13:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, filling this room with carbon\Nmonoxide using just a single grill...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.67,0:13:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would take quite a while and the\Nremaining time wouldn't be sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.72,0:13:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And even if the fire went o ut, it should still retain some heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.60,0:13:37.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, this charcoal...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.31,0:13:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has already been burned and left cold for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.57,0:13:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that means what was placed in the grill\Nwas just charcoal that wasn't on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.28,0:13:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It also means that someone else could've been in this\Nroom to seal the window and door with duct tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.25,0:13:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.87,0:13:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying I was in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, you would've seen me, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.34,0:14:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wasn't here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.96,0:14:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were holding your breath hiding, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.76,0:14:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the space between this bookshelf and the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.97,0:14:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really thought up a good plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.35,0:14:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we saw the door and window all taped\Nup and a charcoal grill on the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.23,0:14:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd think it was a charcoal-burning suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.61,0:14:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And our attention would've been directed\Nto those instead of to the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.86,0:14:30.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enabling you to safely hide behind the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.24,0:14:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just as we were about to remove the tape\Non the window and the grill from the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.58,0:14:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You took the chance to sneak out to the doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.33,0:14:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You attempted to raise the room temperature in order\Nto slow the body temperature's drop rate, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.46,0:14:50.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since his jaw has already begun to stiffen, more\Nthan an hour would've passed since his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His back also showed slight livor mortis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.18,0:14:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's proof that you laid the deceased old man on\Nhis bed to make it appear as if he were sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.81,0:15:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, talk about evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.48,0:15:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her fingerprints are still on the duct tape, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.86,0:15:06.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.98,0:15:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you had to apply the duct tape this sticky...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.65,0:15:12.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would take more time if you had been wearing gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.03,0:15:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet you planned on taking the tape down with us, and trying\Nto trick us by saying that's how your prints got on the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:22.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your plan is ruined, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.04,0:15:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.00,0:15:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who on earth are you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't we tell you when we rang the bell to this house?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.84,0:15:32.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That we're detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.26,0:15:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.05,0:15:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't what I was told!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.89,0:15:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.02,0:15:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what I heard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.35,0:15:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was only a child detective who was coming today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.35,0:15:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.77,0:15:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It was only a child so it's no big deal..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.94,0:15:48.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did this man tell you something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.11,0:15:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.40,0:15:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the culprit who said that everything would be fine if I\Nfollowed the instructions, because I'd be dealing with a child!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.91,0:15:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.37,0:16:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look lady, if you keep spewing nonsense, I'll teach you a lesson!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.46,0:16:04.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.88,0:16:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because when I came here today, Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.51,0:16:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.59,0:16:14.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came in the afternoon as I usually do...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.51,0:16:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I rang the doorbell, no one answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.56,0:16:21.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no choice but to enter using the spare key I was given...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.73,0:16:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the phone had been ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.81,0:16:29.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I answered, the caller told me in\Nan eerie, machine-modified voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.98,0:16:33.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I have shut Kudou up inside his bedroom wardrobe."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.61,0:16:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you want to save him, you'd better hurry," they said...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.87,0:16:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wardrobe?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.79,0:16:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.87,0:16:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came to this room half-unconvinced, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wardrobe had indeed been sealed up with duct tape...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.67,0:16:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a bar had been shoved through the handles,\Nso it couldn't be opened from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.84,0:16:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon after I removed it and opened the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.68,0:16:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.22,0:17:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The edges of the door are sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.47,0:17:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.56,0:17:04.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems they drugged him to sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.23,0:17:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And killed him by locking him up in\Nthere with the burning charcoal grill.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.23,0:17:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You understand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.40,0:17:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That what I'm saying is the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.90,0:17:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.07,0:17:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was indeed the true scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.12,0:17:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was true, why didn't you call the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.37,0:17:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you did something this unwise and were discovered, you\Nknew that the consequences would be irreversible, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.25,0:17:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.88,0:17:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was stuck to the inside of the wardrobe door!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.84,0:17:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A picture of my son!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.22,0:17:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said over the phone that if I didn't do what\NI was told, my son would meet the same fate...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.02,0:17:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you took them seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.94,0:17:48.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.81,0:17:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that person also knew that I often\Ngot into arguments with Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.53,0:17:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And said that camouflaging it as a\Nsuicide would be to my benefit as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:17:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arguments?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.62,0:18:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like over the meals I made.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was picky about his likes and dislikes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.20,0:18:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I've often complained about it to my coworkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.21,0:18:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of meals, what were you planning on doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.75,0:18:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you were going to buy groceries for\Ndinner earlier, but you didn't go, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.43,0:18:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I usually come here after buying groceries at the supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.39,0:18:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was instructed to use those and make\Nit appear as if I had gone shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.10,0:18:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what about dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.56,0:18:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you plan on making?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.44,0:18:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boiled mackerel in soy sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.23,0:18:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean Abukawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the helper?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.73,0:18:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She came here today at noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.15,0:18:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, she was persistent today as well, a tough customer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.62,0:18:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Persistent?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.62,0:18:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the sliced mackerel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.54,0:18:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little of the red juice had collected inside\Nof the pack, so she demanded a discount.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.83,0:18:51.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the price had already been lowered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.33,0:18:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.88,0:18:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like what she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.84,0:19:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might actually be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:05.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she did something as noticeable as\Nhaggling over the price of a fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.35,0:19:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be revealed that her shopping time as an alibi was off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.31,0:19:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And about the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.02,0:19:13.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did they say anything in regards to who they were?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.94,0:19:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.90,0:19:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A vengeful spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.28,0:19:22.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did your caller really identify themselves as that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.87,0:19:24.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.32,0:19:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After they muttered that, the line went dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.95,0:19:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any clues about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.25,0:19:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such as someone who holds a grudge against the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:33.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.04,0:19:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, the victim was an adopted son of the Inubushi\NGroup president, Tsunechika, who died five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.59,0:19:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems he's been frightened about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.30,0:19:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that a bad person had infiltrated the Inubushi family...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.47,0:19:51.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was intent on rooting out everyone with\NInubushi blood using a cursed demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.60,0:19:53.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Demon dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:56.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounds like a story from a mystery novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.73,0:20:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a Holmes story like that wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:02.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that The Inugami Clan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.61,0:20:04.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The Inugami Clan is a mystery novel by\NYokomizo Seishi featuring Kindaichi Kousuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.66,0:20:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, didn't you hear anything from the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.04,0:20:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like if he had a meeting planned with anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.50,0:20:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only heard that a young boy detective from Osaka was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.75,0:20:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the culprit also knew of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.92,0:20:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that this was definitely a crime by an acguaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.11,0:20:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.76,0:20:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he was intending to go out somewhere with that culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.89,0:20:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.22,0:20:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I found him inside the wardrobe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.98,0:20:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was wearing a business suit and necktie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.65,0:20:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Business suit?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.23,0:20:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And necktie?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.52,0:20:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you removed those and put him in a jersey like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.26,0:20:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.61,0:20:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit ordered me to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.12,0:20:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you laid the body on the bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:52.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And waited for the boy detective to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.54,0:20:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you showed off the victim as if he was sleeping...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.92,0:20:58.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you were going shopping and entered the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.67,0:21:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you moved the body to the floor and placed the charcoal grill...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.38,0:21:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And taped up the window and the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.76,0:21:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, you pressed the CD's play button...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.01,0:21:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And hid yourself in a position that would become a blind spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.89,0:21:15.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, when Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s group came in\Nafter being surprised by the CD's music...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.44,0:21:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'd focus on the window, body, and grill, enabling\Nyou to leave the blind spot and move to the doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.11,0:21:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you pretended that you had just returned from shopping...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.41,0:21:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Per the order from the culprit, is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.41,0:21:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.83,0:21:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.16,0:21:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, can you tell me if anything was stolen?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.66,0:21:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.75,0:21:39.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only Kudou san himself would know the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.59,0:21:41.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.17,0:21:45.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ornament attached to his necktie pin was removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.92,0:21:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Necktie pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.76,0:21:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there an expensive jewel attached?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.09,0:21:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.72,0:21:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only noticed that there were signs of\Nsomething having been removed from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.60,0:22:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as what that was, I almost never\Nsee Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in a business suit, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.86,0:22:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Turn him face-up and put him on the stretcher!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.86,0:22:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ready, and... go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.91,0:22:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something fell out of his mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.45,0:22:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was small and round...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.58,0:22:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pearl!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.92,0:22:23.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, investigate that necktie pin right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.84,0:22:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if this man's saliva is on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.18,0:22:35.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This pearl could be the victim's dying message that he\Nbit away from his necktie pin in his final moments!
